.Dd April 19, 2026
.Dt MPORT.FETCH 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm mport.fetch
.Nd download a package bundle from the configured repository
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl c Ar chroot-path
.Op Fl o Ar output-dir
.Op Fl v
.Ar package-name
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
looks up a package in the repository index and downloads the corresponding
bundle file.
Only the first matching repository entry is fetched.
.Bl -tag -width ".Fl o Ar output-dir"
.It Fl c Ar chroot-path
Run inside the specified chroot.
.It Fl o Ar output-dir
Write the downloaded package into
.Ar output-dir
instead of the default package cache.
.It Fl v
Print the selected bundle filename before downloading it.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
Fetch a package into the default downloads directory:
.Dl $ mport.fetch curl
.Pp
Fetch a package into a custom directory:
.Dl $ mport.fetch -o /tmp/packages curl
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr mport 1 ,
.Xr mport.install 1
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
utility appeared in
.Mx 0.3 .
